           <p>First edited by A. Banerji-Sastri (<bibl rend="omitname"><ptr target="bib:BanerjiSastri1940_01"/><citedRange unit="page">246</citedRange><citedRange unit="item">52</citedRange></bibl>), whose reading was reproduced by S. Huntington (<bibl rend="omitname"><ptr target="bib:Huntington1984_01"/><citedRange unit="page">213-214</citedRange></bibl>). An improved edition had by that time already been offered by P.L. Gupta (<bibl rend="omitname"><ptr target="bib:Gupta1965_01"/><citedRange unit="page">155</citedRange><citedRange unit="item">164</citedRange></bibl>). The third edition, by G. Bhattacharya (<bibl rend="omitname"><ptr target="bib:Bhattachatya2000_01"/><citedRange unit="page">95</citedRange></bibl>), is inferior to Gupta’s, as it comprises several silent emendations and printing or typing errors. Although Banerji-Sastri’s summary is presented as such by Huntington and, more curiously, by Bhattacharya, no translation has been published so far.<!-- argr2vito: au lieu de cette phrase, je mettrais simplement "No translation has been published so far."  --> Edited and translated here by Vincent Tournier (09.2020), based on the photograph from the Huntington archive.</p>
